<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#ff7b1c">
  <meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"/>
  <meta property="og:type" content="website"/>
  <meta property="og:site_name" content="Squirrel Chat"/>
  <meta property="og:title" content="Squirrel Chat"/>
  <meta property="og:description" content="Next-gen, open-source and enterprise-ready chat platform"/>
  <meta property="og:image" content="<%= require('@assets/squirrel.png').default %>">
  <link rel="shortcut icon" href="<%= require('@assets/squirrel.ico').default %>">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Open+Sans:wght@400;600;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
</head>
<body>
  <noscript>
    <div class="no-js">
      <img src="<%= require('@assets/squirrel.png').default %>" alt="Squirrel Logo"/>
      <h1>JavaScript is required</h1>
      <p>In order to use the Squirrel Web application, you have to enable JavaScript in your web browser.</p>
      <p>
        If you are worried, Squirrel itself is open-source (BSD-3-Clause) and will not load, or involve in any way
        closed JavaScript code without letting you know what it'll attempt to load, and why.
      </p>
      <div>
        <a href="https://squirrel.chat" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Website</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/squirrelchat/webapp" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Source Code</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </noscript>
  <div id="react-root"></div>
</body>
</html>
